{"DE BENE ESSE":[{"def":"Of well being; of formal sufficiency for the time; conditionally; provisionally.","pos":""}],"DE FACTO":[{"def":"Actually; in fact; in reality; as, a king de facto, -- distinguished from a king de jure, or by right.","pos":""}],"DE JURE":[{"def":"By right; of right; by law; -- often opposed to be facto.","pos":""}],"DE RIGUEUR":[{"def":"According to strictness (of etiquette, rule, or the like); obligatory; strictly required.","pos":""}],"DE-":[{"def":"A prefix from Latin de down, from, away; as in debark, decline, decease, deduct, decamp.","pos":""}]}